2. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses a new modulation scheme that can provide full transmit diversity, which is related to systems and control. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper mentions the code rate of the proposed scheme, which is related to multimedia applications. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the decoding complexity of the proposed scheme, which is related to networking and internet architecture. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper presents a systematic methodology to find the solution sets, which is related to computational engineering.
